    "en": {
      "title": "A case against Vimal is adjourned to December",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo Chief Magistrate Nandana Amarasinghe today (29) adjourned the hearing of the case against former Minister Wimal Weerawansa and six defendants, including former Minister Wimal Weerawansa, to the 12th of December in relation to an incident that allegedly caused public oppression by protesting the arrival of former United Nations Human Rights Commissioner Prince Al Hussain to Sri Lanka. ) ordered.",
        "This order was issued when the defendants related to this incident appeared before the court on bail.",
        "In 2016, when the former United Nations Human Rights Commissioner, Prince Said Al Hussain, visited Sri Lanka, the police had reported to the court that these defendants had protested in front of the United Nations office in Colombo by blocking the highway and causing public distress.",
        "Former Minister Wimal Weerawansa, State Minister Jayantha Samaraweera, Member of Parliament Mohammad Mussammil National Freedom Front members Weerakumara Dissanayake, Piyasiri Wijenayake, and Roger Seneviratne are the other defendants here."
      ],
